  ('Boundary Recovery Drill', 'boundary-recovery-drill', 'The athlete waits for a live cue (coach calls boundary or recovery zone), selects the correct answer, performs the movement response, and resets before the next rep. The rep counts only when the athlete reacts to the real stimulus rather than guessing early.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, 6, 15, 30, 45, 'Boundary Recovery Drill is a reaction-time-reduction drill for reaction to space constraints and safe re-entry. Use it when the goal is faster stimulus recognition, cleaner first movement, and safer reset behavior without turning reaction work into conditioning.', 'Primary subrole: perception_action_reactive_movement. Coach Boundary Recovery Drill as a quality-first reaction drill: define the cue, remove ambiguous starts, require a clean answer, and rest long enough that speed, accuracy, posture, and safety stay intact.', 'See the cue, answer fast, finish clean, then reset. Do not guess before the signal.', 'Spatial Awareness, Multi-Cue, and Game Constraint Reaction', 'movement_intelligence', 'perception_action_reactive_movement', 'boundary_recovery_drill', '{"stimulus":"coach calls boundary or recovery zone","decision_pattern":"recover into space without stepping out","space_needed":"Clear lane, small grid, or box with safe stopping room and no crossing traffic.","setup":"Mark start, finish/reset area, and any target lanes. Explain valid cues and decoy cues before the first rep. Rehearse once at low speed, then randomize the cue.","primary_joint_actions":["hip_flexion_extension","ankle_stiffness","trunk_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["calves","quadriceps","glutes","adductors","core"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["stimulus_discrimination","response_inhibition","first_step_timing","postural_reset"],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"brief brace with relaxed reset breathing","balance_demand":"dynamic balance during reaction and reset","coordination_demand":"high cue-to-action coordination","impact_level":3,"quali